comments: Ayton (PHX) jumps vertically to contest the shot near the rim by Birch (TOR).
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Booker (PHX) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Toronto.

Replay review of the foul called on Booker (PHX) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Booker seals Anunoby's (TOR) body off ball and the contact affects his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and does not deliver contact.
Boucher (TOR) legally contests Crowder (PHX) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Ayton (PHX) and Birch (TOR) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Booker (PHX) is already in Siakam's (TOR) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Siakam's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Siakam's (TOR) path and makes incidental foot to foot contact as they disengage.
Anunoby (TOR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact.
During the loos ball Birch (TOR) makes contact to the ball and makes incidental contact to Ayton's (PHX) arm after contact to the ball.
Anunoby (TOR) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly awarded to PHX.
Crowder (PHX) briefly engages with Birch (TOR) after the pick.
Ayton (PHX) briefly places his forearm to Siakam's (TOR) front and immediately removes it as he defends his drive.
Crowder (PHX) places his arm to VanVleet's (TOR) front and marginal contact occurs defending his drive to the basket.
Paul (PHX) and Birch (TOR) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Boucher (TOR) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Ayton (PHX) jumps vertically and marginal leg to leg contact occurs as Anunoby's (TOR) momentum carries him forward.
Anunoby (TOR) commits a take foul on Paul (PHX).
VanVleet (TOR) commits a take foul on Booker (PHX).
Birch (TOR) and Booker (PHX) briefly engage and disengage with one another during the screen.
Booker (PHX) commits a take foul on Birch (TOR).
VanVleet (TOR) briefly grasps Paul's (PHX) arm off ball and slides his hand off as he gathers the inbound pass.
VanVleet (TOR) commits a take foul on Paul (PHX).
Paul (PHX) commits a take foul on VanVleet (TOR).
Crowder (PHX) makes marginal contact with Boucher's (TOR) jersey during rebounding.
Siakam (TOR) commits a take foul on Ayton (PHX).
